text_blocks.snippet: As of February 7, 2026, the following details pertain to the English artist Kate Bush:

list.snippet: Occupations: Singer-songwriter, musician, record producer, and dancer.
Vocals: Renowned for an ethereal, highly expressive voice with a four-octave range.
Songwriting: A prolific composer and lyricist; she began writing at age 11 and became the first female artist to reach UK No. 1 with a solely self-written song ("Wuthering Heights").
Piano/Keyboards: Highly proficient; taught herself at 11 and uses the piano as her primary songwriting tool.
Record Production: Expert proficiency; she has self-produced all of her studio albums since The Dreaming (1982) and was a pioneer in using digital sampling technology like the Fairlight CMI.
Additional Instruments: Proficient in the organ, violin, and bass guitar.
Choreography/Dance: Trained in interpretive dance and mime under Lindsay Kemp; she choreographed many of her own music videos and integrated theatrical dance into her live performances.

Current Residence: She resides in Oxfordshire, England (specifically at Clifton Hampden Manor) and maintains a home on the Devon coast. (Note: As a UK resident, her location is typically described by county rather than state.)
